# Recipe Spec & Execution

Use `@chrome-ext/automation-recipes` as the canonical schema for recipe steps and locators.

## Recipe Shape (conceptual)

```typescript
type Locator = { by: 'css' | 'role'; selector?: string; role?: string; name?: string };
type StepType =
  | 'goto' | 'waitFor' | 'assertVisible' | 'fill' | 'type' | 'click'
  | 'extract' | 'loop' | 'captureHtml' | 'saveUrl' | 'setVariable'
  | 'saveCheckpoint' | 'restoreCheckpoint' | 'ensureFolder'
  | 'selectDropdown' | 'waitForPagination' | 'navigateBack'
  | 'validateFolder' | 'validateFile' | 'skipIf';
```

## Execution Rules

- Service worker owns orchestration; content scripts execute DOM actions.
- Prefer deterministic selectors (role + name) and include `description` on steps for better logs.
- Retry only idempotent waits; avoid re-clicking if a step already caused navigation.
- Store recipe overrides locally when selector repair is applied; export override JSON for repo updates.

## Packaging

- JSON recipes live in `apps/chrome-extensions/**/src/recipes/jsons/**`.
- Loader/registry registers promoted recipes and merges overrides at startup.
